entry.title: Add event.addRoutes() to InstallEvent
entry.content:
Based on the recent discussion on the Github issue [1], we introduce

`addRoutes()` to InstallEvent, which is another way to register routing

info.



Summary:

1.Unlike `registerRouter()`, `addRoutes()` can be called multiple times.

2.`registerRouter()` remains as it is, at least until OT end date.

3.`addRoutes()` and `registerRouter()` are exclusive. Raises exceptions

once both methods are called.





[1] https://github.com/w3c/ServiceWorker/issues/1373#issuecomment-1667123029

entry.title: media/gpu/v4l2: Teach V4L2StatefulVD to split H.264 NALUs into frames
entry.content:
It turns out that Hana doesn't like to be fed a PPS NALU together with

the first subsequent non-/IDR frame (and many a test vector in the H.264

conformance tests do something like this). Instead, Hana needs to be

fed one full frame at a time -- this is different from Trogdor, whose

only requirement is that whatever is enqueued is not a partial frame.



This CL adds code to the H264FrameReassembler methods to handle this

situation: FindH264FrameBoundaries() is taught to return the location

of the frame boundary (instead of a full frame found yes/no), and

Process() is taught to split frames when they contain more than one

full frame, and to return a vector of DecoderBuffers ready to

enqueue (and their corresponding DecodeCBs).



With this V4L2StatefulVD is closer to parity with the legacy ToT when

it comes to MD5 ChromeStackDecoderVerification for H.264; there's

still some oddities (e.g. CAPCM1_Sand_E.h264 CAPCMNL1_Sand_E.h264

which are left for a later CL to avoid cluttering this one too much).

entry.content:
These files are not appeared in build graph.

By writing it is stored in hashfs, but it won't be written to

disk since it is not in output.

In next build, it detects the file does not exist on disk,

so hashfs does not clean, so need to run schedule but

all steps are up-to-date and finish with "ninja: no work to do".



Without writing these files, build succeeded

and the next build can finish quickly with

"Everything is up-to-date"

entry.title: [ios] Fix NTP Omnibox first defocus animation
entry.content:
When the user taps the unpinned fakebox to focus the omnibox, the NTP

scrolls up to pin the fakebox and then focuses. On defocus, the NTP

should scroll back down to the previous position. But that only worked

on the second defocus - the first time it would just snap back

without animation.



The issue was that a property used to control the timing was not given

the expected initial value, so the first animation was canceled

immediately and the scroll position was set back without animation, and

then the property would get set back to the expected initial value so

that the second animation would work.

entry.title: Remove uses of implicit conversion of ScopedTypeRef in /headless
entry.content:
Implicit unwrapping of a scoper to its underlying pointer is dangerous

and that capability is being removed. This converts uses of implicit

conversion to be explicit so that implicit unwrapping can be removed.

This also may perform other cleanup and modernization.



This was previously landed as https://crrev.com/c/4980610 but was

reverted. This version fixes an issue.
